stories.text:
How do I know if posting a selfie of myself is just "serving the system" or "empowerment"?

Nietzsche is who you'll need to to rebrand any sense of shame into a source of pride.

Marx is the one you'll need to blame others for the shame that lingers when the likes have passed.

And Freud saves the day by turning the whole project into a therapeutic one.

Now you can bring about justice and liberation by going to talk therapy.

For there cannot be a true emancipation without the emancipation of true pleasure and you can't find true pleasure unless you have "worked through your stuff."
